Boil pasta for 10 minutes. Drain. Saute onions in oil in a large saucepan over medium heat until translucent, about 10 minutes. Add garlic and saute another 2 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, herbs, salt, pepper, and 1/4 cup water. Cook uncovered for 20 minutes. Add peas and pasta to sauce. Let simmer for 15 minutes. Serve with sliced mozzarella.